Manchester United sit above Manchester City in the Premier League table for the first time since November 23, 2013 . 
  City lost 2-1 at Crystal Palace on Monday night and trail United by a point . 
  The Red Devils have played the same number of games as City this season . 
  United have only sat above City twice in the post Sir Alex Ferguson era . 
  Louis van Gaal's side face City at Old Trafford on Sunday . 
 